## 6. Element Locating Strategy Priority

Based on the `_parse_locator_strategy` method in BasePage, the priority is:

```python
# Priority 1: AutomationId + ClassName combination
element = self.locate_element(automation_id="btnLogin", type="Button")

# Priority 2: AutomationId alone (recommended - most stable)
element = self.locate_element(automation_id="txtUsername")

# Priority 3: AutomationId shorthand (auto_id)
element = self.locate_element(auto_id="btnLogin")

# Priority 4: Name + ControlType combination (common for menu items)
element = self.locate_element(name="用户管理", control_type="MenuItem")

# Priority 5: Name alone
element = self.locate_element(name="确认")

# Priority 6: ClassName alone
element = self.locate_element(class_name="Button")

# Priority 7: ControlType alone
element = self.locate_element(control_type="Button")

# Priority 8: XPath (complex scenarios)
element = self.locate_element(xpath="//*[@Name='xxx' and @ControlType='Button']")

# Priority 9: TagName
element = self.locate_element(tag_name="Button")
```

